# Personal identity model (curated self-knowledge, not for public repo)
# The base self_model.md is part of the project; user-added identity files stay local
# NOTE: `.identity/*`, NOT `.identity/`. Git cannot re-include a file whose PARENT DIRECTORY is excluded, so
# with `.identity/` the negations below are silently inert — self_model.md only survived because it was added
# before this rule existed. Ignoring the CONTENTS instead lets the negations actually work.
.identity/*
!.identity/self_model.md
# capabilities.md is project content too, not operator state: it is the VERIFIED manifest of what Layla can
# actually do, and it must ship on clone or "preloaded self-knowledge" silently becomes "no self-knowledge"
# and she goes back to inventing capabilities. User-added identity files still stay local.
!.identity/capabilities.md

# Model files (large; each dev supplies their own)
models/*
!models/.gitkeep

# Chroma / vector store persistence (if at repo root)
chroma/
agent/layla/memory/chroma_db/
# Stray Chroma dir if vector_store ever pointed at agent/chroma_db (do not commit index blobs)
agent/chroma_db/
*.sqlite3

